{
  "adpl": "1.1",
  "meta": {
    "name": "Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline — Share Groups, Streams, and Lakehouse Sink",
    "description": "A logistics parcel-tracking pipeline uses Kafka 4.2 Share Groups for true queue semantics with Kafka Streams DLQ routing and Delta Lake sink for lakehouse analytics via DuckDB.",
    "created": "2026-03-16T00:00:00Z",
    "updated": "2026-03-16T00:00:00Z",
    "project": { "name": "Case #017 — Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline", "url": "projects/kafka-streaming-pipeline/index.html", "case_number": "017" },
    "author": "H.A.R.L.I.E. pipeline_builder agent",
    "tags": ["kafka", "python", "dagster", "great_expectations", "data_warehouse", "dashboard"],
    "autonomy_level": "L0",
    "tool": "datainsight.at Pipeline CAD"
  },
  "pipeline": {
    "goal": "Real-time parcel tracking with Kafka 4.2 Share Groups, DLQ routing, and Delta Lake lakehouse sink",
    "nodes": [
      { "id": 1, "subtype": "kafka", "type": "source", "label": "Kafka 4.2", "icon": "📨", "x": 100, "y": 270,
        "config": { "description": "Parcel tracking event stream using Kafka 4.2 Share Groups for true queue semantics and parallel consumer scaling", "broker": "localhost:9094", "topic": "parcel_events", "group": "parcel_share_group" }},
      { "id": 2, "subtype": "dagster", "type": "orchestration", "label": "Dagster", "icon": "💎", "x": 340, "y": 270,
        "config": { "description": "Asset-based orchestration for streaming pipeline with materialisation tracking", "job_name": "parcel_tracking_job", "schedule": "0 * * * *" }},
      { "id": 3, "subtype": "python", "type": "transform", "label": "Python", "icon": "🐍", "x": 580, "y": 150,
        "config": { "description": "Kafka Streams processing: DLQ routing for malformed events, enrichment with carrier data, Delta Lake writer", "script": "stream_transform.py", "function": "run" }},
      { "id": 4, "subtype": "great_expectations", "type": "quality", "label": "Great Expectations", "icon": "✅", "x": 580, "y": 390,
        "config": { "description": "Validate parcel event schema completeness and tracking timestamp ordering", "suite": "parcel_suite", "datasource": "delta_datasource" }},
      { "id": 5, "subtype": "data_warehouse", "type": "serving", "label": "Delta Lake / DuckDB", "icon": "🏛", "x": 820, "y": 150,
        "config": { "description": "Delta Lake table as the lakehouse sink; queried via DuckDB for analytics", "type": "duckdb", "schema": "lakehouse", "table": "parcel_events_delta" }},
      { "id": 6, "subtype": "dashboard", "type": "serving", "label": "Dashboard", "icon": "📊", "x": 820, "y": 390,
        "config": { "description": "Real-time logistics dashboard showing delivery status, delays, and DLQ metrics", "tool": "grafana", "port": "3000" }}
    ],
    "edges": [
      { "id": 1, "fromId": 1, "fromPort": "out-0", "toId": 2, "toPort": "in-0" },
      { "id": 2, "fromId": 2, "fromPort": "out-0", "toId": 3, "toPort": "in-0" },
      { "id": 3, "fromId": 3, "fromPort": "out-0", "toId": 4, "toPort": "in-0" },
      { "id": 4, "fromId": 4, "fromPort": "out-1", "toId": 5, "toPort": "in-0" },
      { "id": 5, "fromId": 5, "fromPort": "out-0", "toId": 6, "toPort": "in-0" }
    ]
  },
  "agents": {
    "setup": {
      "name": "DE Setup Agent",
      "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
      "role": "pipeline setup and testing",
      "goal": "Validate the Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline stack — Kafka 4.2 Share Groups on topic parcel_events, Dagster parcel_tracking_job, Python stream_transform.py with DLQ routing, Great Expectations parcel_suite, and Delta Lake lakehouse.parcel_events_delta — is correctly configured for real-time parcel tracking.",
      "autonomy": "supervised",
      "triggers": ["on_deploy", "on_schema_change", "on_demand"],
      "tools": ["run_compose", "run_health_checks", "run_dbt", "run_integration_tests", "append_exchange_entry"],
      "output_channel": "exchange",
      "system_prompt": "# DE Setup Agent — Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline\n\n## Stack\n- **Source:** Kafka 4.2 (broker: localhost:9094, topic: parcel_events, group: parcel_share_group — Share Groups)\n- **Orchestration:** Dagster (job_name: parcel_tracking_job, schedule: 0 * * * *)\n- **Transform:** Python (stream_transform.py :: run — Kafka Streams, DLQ routing, Delta Lake writer)\n- **Quality:** Great Expectations (suite: parcel_suite, datasource: delta_datasource)\n- **Serving:** Delta Lake / DuckDB (schema: lakehouse, table: parcel_events_delta) | Grafana (port 3000)\n\n## Setup Steps\n1. Confirm Kafka 4.2 broker is reachable at localhost:9094; verify topic `parcel_events` exists and Share Group `parcel_share_group` is registered.\n2. Verify Kafka 4.2 Share Groups feature is enabled on the broker (requires KRaft mode without ZooKeeper).\n3. Verify Dagster loads `parcel_tracking_job` and the `0 * * * *` (hourly) schedule is active.\n4. Run stream_transform.py :: run with a sample parcel event payload; confirm DLQ routing correctly handles a malformed event.\n5. Confirm the Delta Lake writer in stream_transform.py can write to schema `lakehouse` / table `parcel_events_delta`.\n6. Run Great Expectations checkpoint for suite `parcel_suite` against datasource `delta_datasource`; confirm schema completeness and timestamp ordering expectations are defined.\n7. Confirm Grafana is accessible on port 3000 and the logistics dashboard loads with DLQ metric panels.\n\n## Output Protocol\n- **Pass:** Append `{\"status\": \"setup_ok\", \"pipeline\": \"Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline\"}` to exchange.json.\n- **Fail:** Append `{\"status\": \"setup_failed\", \"step\": \"<step>\", \"error\": \"<message>\"}` and halt; await operator instruction.\n\n## Error Handling\n- If Kafka 4.2 Share Groups are not available, halt — this is the core feature of this pipeline.\n- If the DLQ routing in stream_transform.py fails to catch malformed events, flag as critical data loss risk.\n- If Delta Lake table `parcel_events_delta` cannot be created or written to, check DuckDB Delta extension."
    },
    "monitors": [
      {
        "name": "Orchestration Monitor",
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "role": "orchestration health monitor",
        "goal": "Continuously verify that the Dagster job parcel_tracking_job runs on its hourly schedule and that Kafka 4.2 Share Group parcel_share_group maintains healthy consumer throughput.",
        "autonomy": "autonomous",
        "triggers": ["on_schedule:0 * * * *", "on_failure"],
        "tools": ["check_dag_status", "query_run_history", "check_source_timestamps", "append_exchange_entry"],
        "output_channel": "exchange",
        "system_prompt": "# Orchestration Monitor — Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline\n\n## Monitored Job\n- **job_name:** parcel_tracking_job\n- **schedule:** 0 * * * * (hourly)\n- **orchestrator:** Dagster\n\n## Responsibilities\n1. On each trigger, query Dagster for the latest run state of `parcel_tracking_job`.\n2. Compare the last successful run timestamp against the hourly schedule; flag if overdue by more than 10 minutes.\n3. On `on_failure` trigger, retrieve asset-level failure details and append a structured alert to exchange.json.\n4. Monitor Kafka Share Group `parcel_share_group` consumer lag on topic `parcel_events` at broker localhost:9094; flag lag spikes.\n5. Track DLQ event volume per hour; alert if DLQ rate exceeds 5% of total parcel events.\n\n## Output Protocol\n- **Healthy:** Append `{\"status\": \"dag_ok\", \"job_name\": \"parcel_tracking_job\"}` to exchange.json.\n- **Degraded:** Append `{\"status\": \"dag_alert\", \"job_name\": \"parcel_tracking_job\", \"issue\": \"<description>\"}` and notify operator."
      },
      {
        "name": "Data Quality Monitor",
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "role": "data quality monitor",
        "goal": "After each quality run, verify that Great Expectations suite parcel_suite passes against datasource delta_datasource and that parcel_events_delta contains schema-complete, correctly-ordered events.",
        "autonomy": "autonomous",
        "triggers": ["on_quality_run", "on_schedule"],
        "tools": ["read_ge_results", "query_expectations", "compare_run_history", "append_exchange_entry"],
        "output_channel": "exchange",
        "system_prompt": "# Data Quality Monitor — Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline\n\n## Quality Configuration\n- **Suite:** parcel_suite\n- **Datasource:** delta_datasource\n- **Target table:** lakehouse.parcel_events_delta (DuckDB / Delta Lake)\n\n## Responsibilities\n1. After each quality run, read the Great Expectations results for suite `parcel_suite` on datasource `delta_datasource`.\n2. Check for failed schema completeness expectations (missing parcel_id, carrier_code, tracking_timestamp fields).\n3. Validate tracking_timestamp ordering — events must be non-decreasing per parcel_id.\n4. Monitor the DLQ table volume and compare against the main parcel_events_delta table; flag if DLQ exceeds 5%.\n5. Compare the current run's pass rate against the last 7 runs to detect new categories of malformed events.\n\n## Output Protocol\n- **Pass:** Append `{\"status\": \"quality_ok\", \"suite\": \"parcel_suite\"}` to exchange.json.\n- **Alert:** Append `{\"status\": \"quality_alert\", \"suite\": \"parcel_suite\", \"failed_expectations\": [...]}` and escalate."
      },
      {
        "name": "Data Freshness Monitor",
        "model": "claude-sonnet-4-6",
        "role": "data freshness monitor",
        "goal": "Each morning verify that Kafka topic parcel_events at localhost:9094 has active Share Group consumer throughput and that Delta Lake parcel_events_delta contains events processed within the last hour.",
        "autonomy": "autonomous",
        "triggers": ["on_schedule:0 8 * * *"],
        "tools": ["query_row_counts", "check_source_timestamps", "check_mart_freshness", "append_exchange_entry"],
        "output_channel": "exchange",
        "system_prompt": "# Data Freshness Monitor — Kafka 4.2 Streaming Pipeline\n\n## Sources\n- **Kafka 4.2:** broker: localhost:9094, topic: parcel_events, group: parcel_share_group\n- **Delta Lake / DuckDB:** schema: lakehouse, table: parcel_events_delta\n- **Dashboard:** Grafana (port 3000)\n\n## Responsibilities\n1. At 08:00 daily, check Kafka topic `parcel_events` at broker localhost:9094 for consumer lag on Share Group `parcel_share_group`; flag if lag is unexpectedly high or zero.\n2. Query DuckDB Delta Lake table `parcel_events_delta` (schema: lakehouse) for maximum tracking_timestamp; assert events within last 2 hours (given hourly processing).\n3. Compare today's parcel event throughput against the 7-day rolling average; flag drops greater than 20%.\n4. Probe Grafana on port 3000 and confirm the logistics dashboard shows current delivery status and DLQ metrics.\n\n## Output Protocol\n- **Fresh:** Append `{\"status\": \"freshness_ok\", \"source\": \"kafka:parcel_events\"}` to exchange.json.\n- **Stale:** Append `{\"status\": \"freshness_alert\", \"source\": \"kafka:parcel_events\", \"last_seen\": \"<timestamp>\"}` and notify operator."
      }
    ]
  },
  "ahi": { "log": [] },
  "summary": {
    "sources": ["kafka"],
    "transform": "python",
    "orchestration": "dagster",
    "quality": "great_expectations",
    "serving": ["data_warehouse", "dashboard"],
    "agents": []
  }
